verbose_text: Chronic administration of CP to male rats caused testicular toxicity as assessed by glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase, abnormal levels of enzymes (superoxide dismutase (SOD), catalase (CAT), glutathion peroxidase (GPx), glutathion-s-transferase (GST) and glutathion reductase (GR), and antioxidants (reduced glutathion, ascrobate and alpha-tocopherol).
